
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Mining";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}
<nav aria-label="breadcrumb">
    <ol class="breadcrumb">
        <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="~/Home/Index">Home</a></li>
        <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="~/Home/Industries">Industries</a></li>
        <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">Mining</li>
    </ol>
</nav>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">

        <img src="~/Images/pageHeading_mining.png" class="img-fluid d-block" alt="Responsive image">
        <div class="carousel-caption">
            <h3 class="align-self-center">Know about the Risk factors involved with Mining</h3>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="jumbotronmodify container" id="risk">
    <p class="lead">Click on the icon to know more</p>

    <div class="media">
        <img class="btn img-thumbnaill rounded-circle" src="~/Images/gas-mask.svg" data-toggle="collapse" href="#multiCollapseExample1" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="multiCollapseExample1" />
        <p class="lead" style="align-self:center">Hazardous Substances</p>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse multi-collapse " id="multiCollapseExample1">
        <div class=" card-custom">
            <ul class="list-unstyled">
                <li class="media">
                    <img src="~/Images/coal.jpg" class="mr-3 img-thumbnaill rounded img-fluid" alt="...">
                    <div class="media-body">
                        <h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Coal</h5>
                        Long-term exposure to coal powder causes wounds and scars in the lungs. Coal can penetrate the lungs, causing irritation and blocking mucus and water control, leading to serious complications.
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="media my-4">
                    <img src="~/Images/dust.jpg" class="mr-3 img-thumbnaill rounded img-fluid" alt="...">
                    <div class="media-body">
                        <h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Dust</h5>
                        Particles that evade elimination in the nose or throat tend to settle in the sacs or close to the end of the airways. But if the amount of dust is large, the macrophage system may fail. Dust particles and dust-containing macrophages collect in the lung tissues, causing injury to the lungs. The amount of dust and the kinds of particles involved influence how serious the lung injury will be.
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="media">
                    <img src="~/Images/silica.jpeg" class="mr-3 img-thumbnaill rounded img-fluid" alt="...">
                    <div class="media-body">
                        <h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Silicon Dioxide</h5>
                        Silicon dioxide is a silicon oxide, a major component of sand and one of the most abundant substances in the world. Inhalation of finely ground crystalline silicon dioxide infiltrates the lungs and continuously stimulates cellular tissues, reducing lung function.
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="media my-4">
                    <img src="~/Images/asbestos.png" class="mr-3 img-thumbnaill rounded img-fluid" alt="...">
                    <div class="media-body">
                        <h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Asbestos</h5>
                        Asbestos is a class 1 carcinogen, and long-term exposure can cause respiratory diseases such as lung cancer and asbestos lung. There are differences in harmfulness depending on the size, persistence, and amount of asbestos.
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>



    </div>
    <div class="media">
        <img class="btn img-thumbnaill rounded-circle" src="~/Images/lung-cancer.svg" data-toggle="collapse" href="#multiCollapseExample2" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="multiCollapseExample2" />
        <p class="lead" style="align-self:center">Lung Diseases (Click on each disease to know more)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse multi-collapse " id="multiCollapseExample2">
        <div class=" card-custom">
            <ul class="list-unstyled">
                <li class="media">
                    <img src="~/Images/virus.svg" class="mr-3 img-thumbnaill rounded img-fluid" alt="...">

                    <h5 class="mt-0 mb-1"><a href="~/Home/Silicosis">Silicosis</a></h5>

                </li>
                <li class="media my-4">
                    <img src="~/Images/lungs.png" class="mr-3 img-thumbnaill rounded img-fluid" alt="...">

                    <h5 class="mt-0 mb-1"><a href="~/Home/Pneumoconiosis">Pneumoconiosis</a></h5>

                </li>
                <li class="media">
                    <img src="~/Images/lungs.svg" class="mr-3 img-thumbnaill rounded img-fluid" alt="...">

                    <h5 class="mt-0 mb-1"><a href="~/Home/Asbestosis">Asbestosis</a></h5>

                </li>

            </ul>
        </div>

    </div>
    <div class="media">
        <img class="btn img-thumbnaill rounded-circle" src="~/Images/medical-insurance.svg" data-toggle="collapse" href="#multiCollapseExample3" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="multiCollapseExample3" />
        <p class="lead" style="align-self:center">Preventive measures</p>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse multi-collapse " id="multiCollapseExample3">
        <div class=" card-custom">
            <ul class="list-unstyled">
                <li class="media">
                    <img src="~/Images/hazmat.svg" class="mr-3 img-thumbnail rounded-circle img-fluid" alt="...">
                    <div class="media-body">
                        <h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Personal Protective Equipment(PPE)</h5>
                        <p class="pera-bottom mb-30"> Using PPE, control the level of exposure to chemicals and other substances. PPE includes respirators, gloves, goggles and coveralls.</p>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="media my-4">
                    <img src="~/Images/training.svg" class="mr-3 img-thumbnail rounded-circle img-fluid" alt="...">
                    <div class="media-body">
                        <h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Training</h5>
                        <p class="pera-bottom mb-30">Workers need to get educated how to properly handle or use the equipment by providing proper training at the initial stage itself for all kinds of workers which not only includes full-time but also part-time and casual workers. </p>
                    </div>
                </li>


                <li class="media my-4">
                    <img src="~/Images/admin.svg" class="mr-3 img-thumbnail rounded-circle img-fluid" alt="...">
                    <div class="media-body">
                        <h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Administrative controls</h5>
                        <p class="pera-bottom mb-30">Reduce the number of workers exposed during the exposure. This includes job rotation, rest periods, shift or location changes which can make the workers less exposed to the carcinogenic agents that affect their health.</p>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="media">
                    <img src="~/Images/control.svg" class="mr-3 img-thumbnail rounded-circle img-fluid" alt="...">
                    <div class="media-body">
                        <h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Control Monitoring </h5>
                        <p class="pera-bottom mb-30">
                            Ensure the dust that comes out of hazardous substances are removed properly.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </li>

                <li class="media my-4">
                    <img src="~/Images/change.svg" class="mr-3 img-thumbnail rounded-circle img-fluid" alt="...">
                    <div class="media-body">
                        <h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Substitue the substances</h5>
                        <p class="pera-bottom mb-30">Substitute the hazardous substances with safer substances.</p>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="media my-4">
                    <img src="~/Images/eliminate.svg" class="mr-3 img-thumbnail rounded-circle img-fluid" alt="...">
                    <div class="media-body">
                        <h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Eliminate the substances </h5>
                        <p class="pera-bottom mb-30">Remove the hazardous substances that would cause illness or affect the health of workers.</p>
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>

